						               													<description>Throughout the world there are many mysterious places that defy explanation, whose origin or purpose is unknown.  Was the Lost City of Atlantis a real place?  Why do so many ships and planes disappear in the Bermuda Triangle? Was the house in Amityville really inhabited by evil spirits?  The intrigue and mystery invoked by places like these inspired Legends and Lies: Mysterious Locations.  In this expansion each player has a Mysterious Location that  acts as their home base and that grants them a special power or ability that only they can use.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Legends and Lies: Mysterious Locations is an expansion for Legends and Lies card game for two to four players. The four player version can be played with four individual players, two teams of two partners or with The Skeptic expansion four player game where one person acts as the skeptic.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
